  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba3\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b87\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc1\u0bb2\u0bae\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Scholarship for Sri Lankan students in India",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Embassy of India in Colombo has announced Scholarships for Sri Lankans wishing to pursue undergraduate / postgraduate / doctoral courses in Ayurveda, Yoga, Unani, Siddha Medicine and Homeopathy in the academic year 2022-23 under the AYUSH Scholarship Scheme.",
        "The Scholarships are awarded by the Government of India to select talented Sri Lankan citizens in consultation with the Ministry of Education, Sri Lanka.",
        "It is noteworthy that these scholarship plans include all tuition fees and monthly tuition payments, as well as accommodation allowance, annual stipend and health care services.",
        "For more information on this matter, visit the Ministry of Education at www.mohe.gov.lk. Can be found on the website. Applications should be submitted through the ICCR A2A site (www.a2ascholarships.iccr.gov.in) before July 15, 2022 for uploading. Applicants wishing to obtain further information can contact the Indian High Commission in Colombo"
      ],
